  <Subject Subject_ID="300108407">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300000354</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>open-air zoos [300000354], zoos (built complexes) [300000348], complexes by function [300000203], complexes (buildings and sites) [300000202], Built Complexes and Districts (hierarchy name) [300000201], Built Environment (hierarchy name) [300264550], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Distinguished from "wild animal parks" by the lack of restrictions on animal movement and by the mingling of animals and the visiting public, who generally drive through the parks in their own vehicles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se distingue de "instalación para animales salvajes” por la ausencia de restriciones en lo que respecta al movimiento de los animales y por la mezcla que se propicia entre animales y el público visitante, quienes generalmente conducen sus propios vehículos a través del parque.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te onderscheiden van 'dierenparken' door het gebrek aan beperking van de bewegingsvrijheid van de dieren en door het samenbrengen van dieren en bezoekers, die meestal door de parken rijden in hun eigen voertuigen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>與「自然動物園(wild animal parks)」的區別，在於動物的移動不受到限制，動物與參觀者之間沒有隔離，參觀者一般駕駛自己的車輛穿梭動物園中。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
